260.213. No person may knowingly sell, convey or transfer title to any property that
2 contains a permitted or unpermitted solid waste disposal site or demolition landfill, without
3 disclosing [to] the sale, conveyance, or transfer to the department of natural resources.
4 The seller shall inform the buyer early in the negotiation process about the existence and
5 location of the disposal or landfill site. The seller shall also notify the buyer that he may be
6 assuming liability to the state for any remedial action at the site, except that the sale,

