260.330. 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 6 of this section, effective
2 October 1, [1990] 2027, each operator of a solid waste sanitary landfill shall collect a charge
3 equal to [one dollar] two dollars and fifty cents per ton or its volumetric equivalent of solid
4 waste accepted and each operator of the solid waste demolition landfill shall collect a charge
5 equal to [one dollar] two dollars and fifty cents per ton or its volumetric equivalent of solid
6 waste accepted. Each operator shall submit the charge, less collection costs, to the
7 department of natural resources for deposit in the "Solid Waste Management Fund" which is
8 hereby created. On October 1, [1992] 2029, and thereafter, the charge imposed herein shall
9 be adjusted annually by the same percentage as the increase in the general price level as
10 measured by the Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers for the United States, or its
11 successor index, as defined and officially recorded by the United States Department of Labor
12 or its successor agency. [No annual adjustment shall be made to the charge imposed under
